TCP CHAT
========

A simple TCP Chat.


EXECUTION
---------

> - Windows
$ - *NIX

By being in specific directory:

> cd [location of tcp_chat parent]
> python -m tcp_chat [args]

$ cd [location of tcp_chat parent]
$ python -m tcp_chat [args]

By modifying python path:

> set PYTHONPATH=[location of tcp_chat parent]
> python -m tcp_chat [args]

$ PYTHONPATH=[location of tcp_chat parent] \
    python -m tcp_chat [args]

Your own project in different location:

> set PYTHONPATH=[location of my_tcp_chat parent];[location of network-course]
> python -m tcp_chat [args]

$ PYTHONPATH=[location of my_tcp_chat parent];[location of network-course] \
    python -m my_tcp_chat [ars]

Use --help to see usage example of minimal usage:

> python -m tcp_chat --name=user1 --mode=passive
